features: UNIVERSAL TV MOUNT - The TV wall mount fits most 26 to 65 inches LCD, LED, or Plasma flat/curved screens with a weight limit of 88 lbs. Compatible with VESA sizes from 75x75mm to 400x400mm. Model MU0010 is designed for max wall studs with 16" centers. NOTE: Not for alone dry wall application.

OPTIMAL VIEWING EXPERIENCE - Full motion TV mount moves freely to tilt the screen up 5° and down 13° for reducing glare, and swivel TV left or right 45° for comfortable viewing angles. TV bracket provides post-install 3° leveling capability and supports 3.46" to 15.41" wall distance adjust flexibility.

SOLID CONSTRUCTION - Heavy duty TV wall mount with dual 6 support design is constructed of high-quality cold-formed steel for ultimate safety and reliability. Each TV bracket has been strength tested to ensure security for your TV and your family.

EASY MOUNTING SYSTEM - MOUNTUP provides all the necessary hardware in pre-labeled bags, quality template, bubble level, and clear instructions for quick and easy installation. The main part of the TV mount is pre-assembled. Easy install within 15 minutes.
FRIENDLY CUSTOMER SERVICE - Buy MOUNTUP TV wall mount with confidence! TV mount series are backed by 3-year protection. The customer support team is available to answer any questions.

COMPATIBILITY Articulating TV wall mount MU0010 is designed for most 26 to 65 inches LCD, LED, or Plasma flat or curved TVs and is compatible with a max weight of 88 lbs from TCL, Samsung, SONY, Panasonic, Toshiba, VIZIO, Sharp, LG, Philips, etc. Compatible with VESA patterns from 75x75mm to 400x400mm. And allows wood stud spacing between 12 to 16 inches. It also can be mounted on concrete or brick walls. Concrete anchors are not included, they will be sent if needed. Note: Not for alone drywall application. - MU0010 wall mount TV bracket is perfectly compatible with the following TV models(not limited): TCL 32S325, 32S327, 40S325, 43S325, 43S425, 49S325, 50S425, 55R617, 55S425, 55S517. When the wood stud spacing is larger than the standard 16 inch, how we can do? 1st option is using (2 pcs) 2x4's for top and bottom wall plate railing to "bridge" and secure to the main vertical beams that support the building structure. 2nd option we recommend MU0012-24K & MU0028-24K, which fit up max 24" inches wood studs. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Tv wall mount
reviews.reviewText: I used this product to support 50” tv. It was a little heavy but sturdy. It was easy to install and great price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great TV Mount - even on drywall only
reviews.reviewText: Great product! Super easy to install although the instructions are a bit wonky. The range of motion is amazing. Leveling and tilt are easily adjustable. Probably for legal reasons, it says everywhere in the product listing and instructions that it shouldn't be installed on drywall only - must be into studs. I installed on an interior wall that has only flimsy metal studs (typical Florida condo construction), but solid 1/2" drywall. I used six 1/4" x 3" toggle bolts and 1/4" x 1 1/4" fender washers. The bolts have working load limits of 120 lbs. for drywall shear, so unless I have a flood, that thing isn't going anywhere.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I just receive and installed this mount and is really good material and screws are actually metal not cheap aluminum.. was really impressed. Wall mount hole reach 17 inches so gives you plenty of wiggle room for studs at every 16 inches .. highly recommend

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars very sturdy but ease of motion is not so fluid
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. What I Like:Extremely sturdy designEase of installation especially for old style plaster wallsmultiple slotted cut outs allows for a variety of wall stud spacingWhat I don’t like:Two arm design is kinda tight and harder to move than a single armI’ve installed several of these but up till now they’ve all been one arm designs. The two arm design makes it very solid and sturdy, I’ve got only a 50 inch on it, but this thing feels like it could handle much more weight at least upto 65 inches. I like how this design makes it real easy to put the TV up and so when you go to put it up, especially if you’re doing it by yourself, it immediately and easily hooks on to the arm support base and catches it’s weight without leaving you searching hard for it to hook on. I also like how the wall mount base has multiple slotted cut outs all along it’s length that gives you many options outside of the standard 16 inch on center. This was especially nice for me since my house has old style plaster walls that stud finders always fail on and this particular wall it went on was actually 12 inches on center.So far all these are positives. And so the only negative critique I have is that the two arm design makes it harder to move the TV around because the two arms have to move together in a certain way. Pivoting to change minor angles adjustments side to side still work fine, it’s only when you have to move it in a considerable way that it’s a bit difficult. So if you don’t have to move it much and the TV stays pretty much in the same place, this will probably be fine for you. Given all that, at this price point it’s still a very good deal and if I could I’d rate it at a more accurate 4 and a half stars.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars High quality and multifunctional TV mount
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. The process took about ten minutes if you have the proper tools such as a stud finder. The TV mount comes already assembled. The only thing I had to do was connect the two brackets on the TV that it provided, drill some holes, and simply mount. The TV mount has many features, such as forward and backward, tilting at a 20-30 degree angle, small tilt feature for up and down and side to side on the actual TV. This TV mount has the same features as my more expensive TV mount in my living room. I would buy an exact TV from the same company if I had to install another TV mount. The package came with many different nails and other things, but I simply used only 2 wall nails and did not use any of the other nails or tools that came with it. Very simple installation.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good Quality, Good Price
reviews.reviewText: Bought this to hang a 50 inch TV in my bedroom and was nervous of the quality upon opening. To my surprise, all the parts are made from high quality metal and instructions were easy to follow. I liked it so much i recommended one to my mom.Pros:*High quality material. Feels very sturdy*Easy install - Very easy to follow instructions with pictures (i'm a visual person). There is a template provided to help with bolt placement and level install.*Bubble level included.*Additional pieces included - Multiple install methods depending on you set up and all parts are included.Cons:*The spacing where I wanted to install only fit 1 stud and therefore had to use toggle bolts to securing fasten the other side.Overall great product and will order again if needed.
